CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 17, 1954, pg. 13, reads: "Symposium Principals - When Atty. Carmel Carrington Marr, adviser to Ambassador Henry Cabot Lodge Jr., U.S. Representative to the United Nations, came here to be the main speaker at the National Achievement Clubs' annual Palm Sunday Symposium, she was tendered a luncheon by the family of steel executive Aaron Levinson, at his palatial home on Forbes Street. in first photo, left to right, are shown, seated: Attorney Marr, Mrs. S.M. Levinson, Warren Marr II, Mrs. Alma Illery, and the children, Jimmy Levinson and Estelle Grady Jr. In the rear are Aaron Levinson, Mrs. Goldie Hamilton, S. M. Levinson and Mrs. Mary Clark..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, standing from left: Aaron Levinson, Goldie Hamilton, S. M. Levinson, Mary Clark; seated Atty. Carmel Carrington Marr, Mrs. S. M. Levinson, Warren Marr II, Alma Illery; and Jimmy Levinson and Estelle Grady Jr. on floor; in Levinson home, Forbes Street
